<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" Description="This caldef file defines the AM specific tuner calibrations.  These calibrations are primarily defined to configure the tuner for specific regions.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>14</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>May 8, 2014</Date>
    <Description>Dropped AM_ScanThreshold1 and AM_ScanThreshold2 as scanning is no longer supported.</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>29SEP14</Date>
    <Description>Add Usage on all components</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>December 1, 2014</Date>
    <Description>Cal Def File Version 4.  December 1, 2014:  
Here is a summary of the changes for this release:

1.  Deleted AM_Range Type Integer and replaced with Enumeration AM_Range_Definition from GIS653_AMTuner.enumdef.  Cal was incorrectly defined as an integer value.

2.  Deleted AM_StepSize Type Integer and replaced with Enumeration AM_Range_Definition from GIS653_AMTuner.enumdef.  Cal was incorrectly defined as an integer value.

3. Deleted AM_AutoC_Level and AM_Autostore as these features are no longer used for Info 3 programs.   

4. AM_TimeToProductAudio. Added this calibration to define the time in msec to delay producing audio after a preset selection, seek/tune, or direct tune process before audio is played to allow for system dynamic switching conditions to dissipate.  See GMW16273.

5.  AM_AGC_Threshold.  This calibration defines the AM Band AGC thresholds for a specific region as defined in GMW16273.</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>06Feb2015</Date>
    <Description>The following changes were made to this GIS-653 AM Tuner caldef file:
 1. AM_AGC_Threshold.  Added usage HIGH, MID, LOW as this was not    previously defined.  Corrected mapping problem to the enum value as it showed invalid in previous release.

2.  Deleted AMFM_FastTuneRate and AMFM_FastSeekRate as they are already defined in the AMFMTunerCommon.caldef file and therefore redundant cals.

3. Changed cal type for AM_Seek to an enum to match the enum values defined in GIS653AMTuner.enumdef.  Removed reference to GIS-1-205 as this specification is obsolete and has been replaced by GMW16273.

3. Corrected description for AM_SeekC_HighLevel and AM_SeekCLowLevel to change reference from FMSeekC to AMSeekC. 

4. Changed description for AM_Noise as it was not correct.

5.  Added the following calibrations to address the Assembla ticket for tuner reception performance calibrations exposed to the caldef files by Harman.  This contain the SS prefix to indicate these are supplier specific calibrations.  Harman should use this designation plus the High/Mid Usage field to query these cals from the database.

SS_AM_SoftMuteResponse
SS_AM_SoftMuteStart
SS_AM_SoftMuteSlope 
SS_AM_SoftMuteLimiter
SS_AM_IFBandwidthControlParameter</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>4/17/2015</Date>
    <Description>Per request from Sanghyun Ryu updated AM_Noise cal in this caldef file to remove usage of Low Radio.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>25-Jun-2015</Date>
    <Description>The following changes have been implemented for this release:&#xD;
1. Added new Cals:&#xD;

    BrazilAMBandDisable for pending Brazlian AM regulations. 
    AntennaPhantomPowerCycleTime to support Antenna diagnostics defined in GIS-653. 
    AM_AntMastSignalThreshold for strong station threshold.  
    AM_SeekStopCount.  For minimum SeekStops.
    AntennaConfiguration. For whether the mast antenna is included.&#xD;

2.  Also added these to support direction from GM-Harman workshop to eliminate enum in favor of specific values
    AM_Stop_Frequency 
    AM_Start_Frequency
    AM_Step_Size&#xD;

3.Deleted the AM_Range CAL&#xD;
</Description>
    <Author>Kiran Soni</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>03.09.2015</Date>
    <Description>Changed description and default values of the following supplier-specific parameters: SS_AM_SoftMuteStart, SS_AM_SoftMuteSlope, SS_AM_SoftMuteLimiter.</Description>
    <Author>Christian Gross</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>3/10/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS653_AMTuner.caldef file per recommendation from Dennis Ward and Don Hibbard from GM Validation, updated the maximum value for the AM_SeekC_HighLevel CAL from 60 to 100 to provide the maximum capability of the first pass seek high threshold so that the range of values can accomodate any possible vehicle line variations needed to meet GMW16273 requirements.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS653_AMTuner.caldef file, added GEM usage to the following calibrations within this caldef: (1.) BrazilAMBandDisable, (2.) AntennaConfiguration, (3.) AM_FM_FastTuneRate, (4.) AM_Step_Size, (5.) AM_Start_Frequency, (6.) AM_Stop_Frequency, (7.) AM_Seek, (8.) AM_AGC_Threshold, (9.)AntennaPhantomPowerCycleTime, (10.) AM_TimeToFirstAudio, (11.) AM_SeekC_HighLevel, (12.) AM_SeekStopCount, (13.) AM_AntMastSignalThreshold, (14.) AM_SeekC_LowLevel, and (15.) AM_SoftMute. Since these calibrations fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>05/10/2018</Date>
    <Description>GMW16273 related changes. Per CR#1768009, deleted AM_AGC_Threshold, and AM_SoftMute calibrations from GIS653_AMTuner.caldef. Updated the default value for the AM_Seek calibration to the enumeration value of AM_Seek_Threshold_C</Description>
    <Author>Christine Marzan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>6/19/2019</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#2303157 AOSP transition, updated description for cal BrazilAMBandDisable. In MY22 GIS-646 Cal DB V6.0.3, deprecating the following cals AntennaConfiguration, AM_SeekStopCount, AM_AntMastSignalThreshold as Mast Installation Verification test requirements were not implemented. </Description>
    <Author>Christine Marzan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
