  <CalDefinition Description="Creates a cycle time for toggling the phantom power On-Off time as defined in specific profile of conducting this test.  Cycles times will be on the order of msecs.  For example if this cal is set to 200 msecs, it means the tuner shall apply phantom power for 200 msec and then immediately turn the phantom power off." Name="AntennaPhantomPowerCycleTime" References="GIS-653-7500" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_HsQB8RtvEeWeKtb2c1Y4bg</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
